entry.title: The Great Trafalgar Square Freeze
entry.content: The day London froze. Inspired by www.ImprovEverywhere.com and made a reality by 100's of volunteers. At exactly 3 on a secret cue, almost everyone in the square froze. The few bewildered tourists didn't know what was happening. For 5 minutes the participants held their positions, and then magically everyone unfroze. Why? Well, why not. *** This video and soundtrack are now released as Creative Commons Attribution. Feel free to reuse / reedit however you want - just let me know what you've done. Thanks ***

entry.title: Spandy Andy Dancing in London during the Olympics in his Budgy Smugglers
entry.content: If you liked the video of me dancing in my sparkly speedo on the beach in Australia, wait until you see what I do with my Budgy Smugglers (www.BudgySmugglers.com) in London during the Olympics! I'm currently in London, England to experience the 2012 Olympics and I received a bunch of tight, bright swimwear from Budgy Smugglers so I had to show them off in the only way I know how - with some surprising displays of dancing in public places! I dance in front of Buckingham Palace, on the Tube, in Trafalgar Square, at Piccadilly Circus, near the Tower Bridge, by the London Eye, and even in front of a castle! You can see some pretty iconic stuff like double decker busses, the countdown clock to the Olympics, and even the Olympic rings. You can see the video of me dancing at St. Kilda beach in Melbourne at http (almost 5 million views!) The song in this video was custom made by MikS Music: www.miksmusic.com Thanks to my brother Josh Rimer for doing the videography and editing of this video - check out his comedy videos at http And thanks to my girlfriend Lycra Lindsey for being my (very) personal assistant! COMING SOON: I'll have behind the scenes footage and full videos of each spot that I danced in at www.youtube.com --- Subscribe for more and connect with me at these other places online: Website: www.SpandyAndy.com Facebook www.facebook.com Twitter: www.twitter.com Instagram: SpandyAndy

entry.title: Jacque Fresco - The Venus Project | London Real
entry.content: London Real meets Futurist Jacque Fresco of The Venus Project TWEET this video Click clicktotweet.com FULL EPISODE www.youtube.com More episodes on www.youtube.com LIKE us on Facebook @ www.facebook.com FOLLOW us on Twitter @ twitter.com LISTEN IN ITUNES:itunes.apple.com BONUS FOOTAGE on www.londonreal.tv enter your EMAIL to receive Futurist and Legendary Creator Jacque Fresco travels from Florida to London to discuss The Venus Project, his candid conversation with Albert Einstein as a young boy, what happened with Peter Joseph and The Zeitgeist Movement, how the Great Depression developed his mindset, and what he would do if elected President of the United States. "Creativity is taking known elements and putting them together in different ways." - Jacque (01 "There are no good or bad people, people are shaped by culture or subcultures that they're part of." - Jacque (02:49) "I spoke at Princeton and I titled the lecture 'Man Can't Think or Reason', that made everybody angry and they all wanted to come." - Jacque (04:10) "They say people invented language to communicate. That's strictly BS, bad science." - Jacque (05:50) "When I was a kid I met Einstein and I said, 'Do you believe in God?' and he said, 'Which one?'" - Jacque (07:08) "So for the Venus Project that means you didn't invent anything?" - Brian (08:36) "Today they say this man is good, this man is autistic, this man is gifted. All bullshit." - Jacque (14:39) "Are there leaders in The Venus Project?" "No there ...

entry.title: From London With Love
entry.content: The best time of my life in visuals. I learnt and realized so much from the trip. Despite many shortcomings (ie not hitting pre-trip expectations, not meeting the guys that I intended to meet, didn't have the opportunity to travel to all the spots), I still am thankful that I met so many people and experienced so much in this travel. Honestly, a video wouldn't do justice to how great the trip was - you have to be there experience it. But this is probably the closest I could get. So much thanks to the guys who gave us a place to stay when we went over, namely Mike and Zak. And of course to the people who trained with us: Flynn, Gareth, Chris, Barry, Jake, Elijah, Lish, Luqman, Ross, Jay, Alex Pepper. Not forgetting most especially the Belgian guys who went over to Cambridge with us: Zaur, Pieter, and Gio! And also the Feline Family guys (Tim, Nico and Jasper!) and the Scots (Smillie and Lewis!). Lastly but not least, the Cambridge guys: Ozzy, Charlie, Luke, Harry! I'm pretty sure I missed out a few names but massive, massive love to you guys!!! I WILL be back for sure! Camera/Lenses: Canon EOS 550D, 17-50mm f2.8 Tamron Edited with: All in Sony Vegas! Song: Uzi and Ari - Mountain/Molehill Inspiration for Edit: Isenseven. So gooooood Enjoy. PS: I still have a HUGE bunch of clips left so stay tuned for a second video.

entry.title: London's Police Secrets - Funniest Police Video Ever
entry.content: See behind the scenes at the ANPR (Automatic Number Plate Recognition) computer cars and vans as London's Metropolitan Police catch motorists without insurance as they drive along. See London's "Cycle Police", with POLICE written on their bottoms, stop cyclists in Whitehall - and see them chase a speeding Jaguar car into Trafalgar Square, whilst still on their bicycles. Remember, British Police don't carry guns, so you must stop when they shout "STOP". If you don't, they have to shout it again. And you'll get frowned at.

entry.title: Fifty People, One Question: London
entry.content: What might happen when we venture far from home now? Will we find that London light around the corner? Will the rain hide all the dreamers out of sight? They might not want to play our little game this time - or we could look away and miss our chance. Or maybe just a bit of something out there will remind us why we take the time to ask. It's a simple question and the answers can lead us anywhere. So go ahead, ask yourself Visit fiftypeopleonquestion.com and post your response. We also asked this question in Brooklyn, NY - fiftypeopleonequestion.com/locations/3-brooklyn-ny

It's a simple question and the answers can lead us anywhere. So go ahead, ask yourself Visit fiftypeopleonquestion.com and post your response. We also asked this question in Brooklyn, NY - fiftypeopleonequestion.com/locations/3-brooklyn-ny

entry.title: Caught Up 2012- (London Show Soundcheck)
entry.content: Here is a clip of myself and the FRO(Funk Rock Orchestra) during sound check before this show in London...It was really a lot of fun!!!! I really wish you could hear a little more of the band but I'll try to get a better mix one of these days...You are stuck with this one for now...Sorry...I was checking out the way I played this back in 2006 compared to the way I play it now...It's definitely different...I really hope you all like it...If you don't, that's cool too...No worries...Thank you for taking the time to check it out and for your support...Be safe!!!
